justification:
Oakleaf is quite bold and shows the influence of Morris in its wandering, all-over oak branch design.&amp;nbsp; 
Cobwebs is strong graphically but is printed in very muted colors, which is Marthe's preferred color palette.&amp;nbsp; The flatness of her designs is reminiscent of Pugin and Bawden. &amp;nbsp;
Both designs are current production from 2004 and were printed by linoleum block on a manual offset lithographic printing press.&amp;nbsp;
